column4: description:"The Pearson Student Coding Contest is designed to reward Contestants who develop relevant
column8: and original applications that integrate with the Pearson APIs. The 2014 Contest is open and limited to students who are enrolled in an undergraduate institution within the United States and Canada (excluding Quebec).\\r\

column17: description:"Who participates in Local Hack Day?\\r\

column1: Any student is welcome to participate. Individual events may have different requirements regarding age and student status. All hack days follow the MLH Code of Conduct to ensure a welcoming environment for hackers and a publicly available reporting system for incidents.\\r\
Each event during Local Hack Day kicks off 9:00 am local time December 6th and lasts until 9:00 pm local time.\\r\
What do I if there isn\'t a Local Hack Day event near me?\\r\
You can host one! Check out our guidelines and suggestions for hosting an event.\\r\
You can build anything you want. Make sure to bring any hardware
column2: laptops or smart-phones that you want to utilize during the event.\\r\

column1: What if I\'ve never been to a hackathon before?\\r\
A hack day is the perfect chance for you to experience what a Hackathon is like. Regardless of experience level
column2: all are welcome to come learn

column1: Each Local Hack Day will start with a team formation workshop to help you find a team if you don\'t have one. You don\'t need to have a team to participate though."
